    <h1 class="mb-6">AI Overviews Optimisation Agency</h1>
    <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-8">By Adam Parker | Updated May 2026</p>
    <div class="bg-off-white border-l-3 border-l-teal rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[15px] text-teal font-medium leading-relaxed m-0">A UK agency that gets your business cited inside Google AI Overviews. The AI-generated answer now sits above the ten blue links on Google for most UK queries. Being cited there is the difference between organic traffic and being invisible.</p>
    </div>
<p class="answer-capsule text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">AI Overviews are the Google-generated answer block at the top of search results. Around 63% of US Google queries already trigger an AI Overview and the rollout is accelerating in the UK. AI Overviews optimisation is the work of making your business one of the named sources Google quotes inside that answer.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">What AI Overviews actually are</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">AI Overviews are powered by Gemini and trained against the Google search index. When a user asks a question, Gemini drafts an answer in real time, draws from a small set of cited sources, and renders the answer above the organic results. The user reads the answer first. Around half the time they never click through. Of the clicks that do happen, around 70% go to the named sources inside the Overview.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Semrush research shows the citation set is dominated by pages already ranking in Google's top 10 organic results for the same query. Around 70% of AI Overview citations come from page one. That means traditional SEO authority is the foundation. Without page-one rankings, AI Overview citation is rare.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">On top of authority, AI Overviews favour pages with clear answer capsules, named authors, factual claims with sources, comparison tables, and the right structured data. Pages that match this shape are cited at roughly three times the rate of pages with the same authority but unstructured content.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Why AI Overviews matter more than other AI platforms in the UK</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Google holds 92.7% UK search market share. Every UK search query is now an AI Overview opportunity. ChatGPT and Perplexity matter, but their UK reach is a fraction of Google's. Optimising for AI Overviews is the single highest-volume AI search move a UK business can make.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The same work that lifts AI Overview citation also lifts Gemini citation, ChatGPT Browse citation (Bing-indexed), and Microsoft Copilot citation. AI Overviews optimisation is the foundation. The other platforms reuse the same signals.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Our AI Overviews optimisation services</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">We work the four levers that move AI Overview citation: traditional ranking authority, content shape, structured data, and entity recognition.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5"><strong>Ranking authority foundation:</strong> Because 70% of AI Overview citations come from page one, we start with the SEO fundamentals. Topical depth, internal linking, technical foundation, and content production for the queries that matter to your business.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5"><strong>Answer capsule restructuring:</strong> AI Overviews quote concise factual passages. We rewrite key pages so the answer sits in a short capsule at the top of the content, with the question phrased as an H2 directly above. This is the shape AI Overviews actually lift from.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5"><strong>Schema and structured data:</strong> Organization, Article, FAQPage, Speakable, HowTo and Person schema applied with a connected @graph structure. The graph tells Google that your business, your authors, your pages and your services are one entity network rather than disconnected fragments.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5"><strong>Knowledge Graph and entity work:</strong> Wikidata entries, Knowledge Graph audits, Companies House and Crunchbase reinforcement, ensuring third-party sources describe your business consistently. AI Overviews cite businesses that Google recognises as entities first and unknown websites a distant second.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5"><strong>Citation tracking:</strong> We monitor which queries trigger AI Overviews for your category, which sources Google cites, and where you appear or do not. The data feeds back into the content plan every cycle.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Typical engagement and cost</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Most UK businesses see first measurable AI Overview citation lifts 60 to 90 days into an engagement, with material impact at 4 to 6 months. Entity work moves fastest. Citation rates for AI Overviews specifically depend on Google re-indexing your improved pages, which is the slowest variable.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">UK AI Overviews optimisation engagements typically run £1,500 to £5,000 per month for SMEs and £5,000 to £25,000 per month for enterprise programmes. We work in scoped phases so you can stop at any quarter boundary without contract overhang.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Why choose us</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Rank4AI was built from the ground up for AI search. AI Overviews is one of six platforms we cover. The Five Signal Model maps directly to the citation signals AI Overviews use, and we have applied it to over 40 UK businesses across regulated finance, professional services and e-commerce.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Start with a free audit. We test your visibility across AI Overviews, Gemini, ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity and Copilot and show you the gap.</p>
